R
3
) as well as 3.73% (element
C
1
), 1.85% (element
C
2
) and 1.05% (element
C
3
) in the considered SOC range from 10% to 100%. The parameter identification scripts are provided in the dataset linked in the Section ’Data availability’. An overview with the dynamic parameters of the 3 RC elements is given in Fig. 5. A comparison of simulated and measured CC discharges shows a maximum deviation of 102mV at 90% depth of discharge (DOD) and < 20mV at a DOD below 80% for a C/3 discharge. When comparing C/20 discharges, deviations of < 10mV emerge up to 80% DOD, deviations of maximum 55mV only arise at a higher DOD.
